          <Comment>For these reasons, this variant has been classified as Pathogenic. ClinVar contains an entry for this variant (Variation ID: 1452522). This variant has not been reported in the literature in individuals affected with POT1-related conditions. This variant is present in population databases (no rsID available, gnomAD 0.0009%). This sequence change creates a premature translational stop signal (p.Asn441Lysfs*2) in the POT1 gene. It is expected to result in an absent or disrupted protein product. Loss-of-function variants in POT1 are known to be pathogenic (PMID: 32155570).</Comment>
