          <GermlineClassification>Pathogenic</GermlineClassification>
          <Comment>The c.1322dupA variant, located in coding exon 10 of the POT1 gene, results from a duplication of A at nucleotide position 1322, causing a translational frameshift with a predicted alternate stop codon (p.N441Kfs*2). This alteration is expected to result in loss of function by premature protein truncation or nonsense-mediated mRNA decay. As such, this alteration is interpreted as a disease-causing mutation.</Comment>
