          <GermlineClassification>Likely pathogenic</GermlineClassification>
          <Comment>The POT1 c.1322dup (p.Asn441LysfsTer2) variant, to our knowledge, has not been reported in the medical literature. This variant is only observed on 1/250,876 alleles in the general population (gnomAD v.2.1.1), indicating it is not a common variant. This variant causes a frameshift by inserting a single nucleotide, leading to a premature termination codon, which is predicted to lead to nonsense mediated decay. Loss-of-function variants in POT1 are known to be pathogenic (Gong Y et al., PMID: 32155570). This variant has been reported in the ClinVar database as a pathogenic germline variant by two submitters. Based on available information and the ACMG/AMP guidelines for variant interpretation (Richards S et al., PMID: 25741868), this variant is classified as likely pathogenic.</Comment>
